            "title": "Whole-Home Generator Installation Protects Family During Summer Power Outage",
            "location": "Tortolita, Dove Mountain Ranch",
            "challenge": "Tortolita family with young children (ages 3, 5, and 8) contacted us in June 2024 after experiencing a frightening 22-hour power outage during a severe monsoon storm in late May. During the outage, interior temperatures reached 102°F by afternoon (dangerous for small children), food spoilage cost $380 in groceries and frozen meals, children couldn't sleep in extreme heat, no way to prepare meals or bottles, garage door opener didn't work (couldn't access vehicles), and growing anxiety about future outages during Arizona's intense summer. Additionally, the father works from home requiring reliable power for his tech job, and the mother has asthma requiring continuous power for nebulizer equipment. Living in newer Tortolita development with buried utilities, they had experienced 4 outages in 18 months from monsoon damage, utility work, and equipment failures.",
            "solution": "Our comprehensive assessment recommended a 22kW Generac air-cooled generator with natural gas fuel providing unlimited runtime. Installation included detailed electrical load calculation supporting dual 3-ton AC units (essential cooling for family with young children), all kitchen appliances and refrigeration, home office equipment (router, computers, monitors for work-from-home), garage door openers (emergency vehicle access), nebulizer and medical equipment outlets, lighting throughout home, master bedroom ceiling fan for sleep comfort, and communication systems. We coordinated natural gas service with Southwest Gas, installed automatic transfer switch ensuring 15-second power restoration, positioned generator for optimal noise reduction (40 feet from neighbor's property line), added whole-home surge protection (protecting $22,000 in electronics, appliances, and home office equipment), completed all permits and city of Marana inspections, provided comprehensive homeowner training including weekly auto-exercise cycle, and scheduled annual preventive maintenance plan.",
