            "challenge": "Tortolita homeowners in their early 60s planning for eventual retirement and aging-in-place contacted us about smart home integration to enhance security, convenience, and energy efficiency. Concerns included difficulty operating light switches (arthritis beginning to affect dexterity), security anxiety when traveling (no video monitoring or remote control), energy waste from forgetting to turn off lights and adjust thermostats, complexity of operating ceiling fans, thermostats, and other controls, desire to monitor home remotely when away, and future-proofing home for eventual mobility limitations. Previous smart home consultation from national retailer recommended $28,000 system requiring complete home rewiring, which seemed excessive. They wanted professional integration but at reasonable cost for their 2,800 sq ft home.",
